---
layout: post
title: "Peanut Stew"
date: 2020-10-15
permalink: /peanut-stew
tags: vegan vegetarian

---

Ingredients:
  * olive oil
  * garlic, 4 cloves, minced
  * ginger, grated, 1 TBSP
  * sweet potato, cubed, ~1 lb
  * onion, 1 medium, diced
  * cumin
  * crushed red pepper
  * tomato paste, 6 oz
  * natural peanut butter, 1/2  cup
  * vegetable broth
  * collard greens or kale or spinach, chopped, 1/2 bunch
  * salt, to taste

Steps:
  1. saute onion, garlic, and ginger until onion is translucent, ~3 minutes
  1. add sweet potato, cumin, and red pepper, saute 5 minutes
  1. add tomato paste, peanut butter, and broth, stir until peanut butter and tomato paste are dissolved
  1. boil 20 minutes
  1. stir in the greens, let simmer 5 more minutes
  1. smash some sweet potatoes against the side of the pot to thicken the stew

Yields 6 servings.

Serve over brown rice.
Top with cilantro and chopped peanuts
